{"metadata":{"symbolKind":"struct","modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"CondRef","kind":"identifier"}],"roleHeading":"Structure","title":"CondRef","externalID":"s:4GLib7CondRefV","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"CondRef","kind":"identifier"}]},"sections":[],"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"CondRef"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","text":"Overview","anchor":"overview","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Consider the following example of a shared variable.  One or more"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"threads can wait for data to be published to the variable and when","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"another thread publishes the data, it can signal one of the waiting","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"threads to wake up to collect the data.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Here is an example for using GCond to block a thread until a condition"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"is satisfied:","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"(C Language Example):"}]},{"code":["  gpointer current_data = NULL;","  GMutex data_mutex;","  GCond data_cond;","","  void","  push_data (gpointer data)","  {","    g_mutex_lock (&data_mutex);","    current_data = data;","    g_cond_signal (&data_cond);","    g_mutex_unlock (&data_mutex);","  }","","  gpointer","  pop_data (void)","  {","    gpointer data;","","    g_mutex_lock (&data_mutex);","    while (!current_data)","      g_cond_wait (&data_cond, &data_mutex);","    data = current_data;","    current_data = NULL;","    g_mutex_unlock (&data_mutex);","","    return data;","  }"],"syntax":"C","type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Whenever a thread calls ","type":"text"},{"code":"pop_data()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" now, it will wait until","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"current_data is non-","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"type":"text","text":", i.e. until some other thread"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"has called ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"push_data()"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The example shows that use of a condition variable must always be","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"paired with a mutex.  Without the use of a mutex, there would be a","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"race between the check of "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"current_data"},{"text":" by the while loop in","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"pop_data()"},{"text":" and waiting. Specifically, another thread could set","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"current_data","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" after the check, and signal the cond (with nobody"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"waiting on it) before the first thread goes to sleep. ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Cond"},{"type":"text","text":" is"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"specifically useful for its ability to release the mutex and go"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to sleep atomically."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"It is also important to use the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_cond_wait()"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_cond_wait_until()"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"functions only inside a loop which checks for the condition to be","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"true.  See ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_cond_wait()"},{"type":"text","text":" for an explanation of why the condition may"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"not be true even after it returns.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If a "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Cond"},{"type":"text","text":" is allocated in static storage then it can be used"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"without initialisation.  Otherwise, you should call ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_cond_init()"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"on it and ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_cond_clear()"},{"type":"text","text":" when done."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Cond","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" should only be accessed via the g_cond_ functions.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/CondRef"},{"type":"text","text":" type acts as a lightweight Swift reference to an underlying "},{"code":"GCond","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" instance."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"It exposes methods that can operate on this data type through ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/CondProtocol","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" conformance."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Use "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/CondRef","isActive":true},{"text":" only as an ","type":"text"},{"code":"unowned","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" reference to an existing "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GCond"},{"type":"text","text":" instance."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"aside","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Use ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Cond"},{"type":"text","text":" (instead of "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/CondRef","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":") if you want to use Automatic Reference Counting for memory management of the underlying "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GCond"},{"type":"text","text":" instance."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"name":"Note","style":"note"}]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib"]]},"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/CondRef"},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Cond"},{"text":" struct is an opaque data structure that represents a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"condition. Threads can block on a ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Cond","isActive":true},{"text":" if they find a certain","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"condition to be false. If other threads change the state of this"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"condition they signal the ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Cond"},{"text":", and that causes the waiting","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"threads to be woken up."}],"topicSections":[{"generated":true,"title":"Initializers","anchor":"Initializers","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/CondRef\/init(_:)-3vuu1","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/CondRef\/init(_:)-5lwo4","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/CondRef\/init(_:)-64xk6","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/CondRef\/init(_:)-858ub","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/CondRef\/init(_:)-d6nf","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/CondRef\/init(cPointer:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/docume